. Well, this is embarrassing. Today, after weeks of fiddling with Flight, I got DEBUG to work on my project. What I was doing wrong was trying to require my `default.js` (in terms of the Flight generator) in the main require:

``` javascript
require(
  [
    'flight/lib/compose',
    'flight/lib/registry',
    'flight/lib/advice',
    'flight/lib/logger',
    'flight/lib/debug',
    'page/default'
  ],

  function (compose, registry, advice, logger, debug, initializeDefault) {
    debug.enable(true);
    initializeDefault();
  }
);
```

DEBUG seems to work only when I put

``` javascript
require(['page/default'], function (initializeDefault) {
  initializeDefault();
});
```

inside the function block above, which effectively ensures debug has been set up before `page/default` is loaded — I should've known that. Either has no effect on the overall functionality of my app — the events get fired regardless.
